infodynamics.measures.continuous.kernel

Class PredictiveInfoCalculatorKernel

  • java.lang.Object
    • infodynamics.measures.continuous.PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo
      • infodynamics.measures.continuous.kernel.PredictiveInfoCalculatorKernel
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    InfoMeasureCalculatorContinuous, PredictiveInfoCalculator, EmpiricalNullDistributionComputer

    public class PredictiveInfoCalculatorKernel
extends PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo
    A Predictive Information (PI) / Excess Entropy calculator (implementing PredictiveInfoCalculator) which is affected using a box-kernel Mutual Information (MI) calculator (MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKernel) to make the calculations.

    That is, this class implements a PI calculator using box-kernel estimation. This is achieved by plugging in MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKernel as the calculator into the parent class PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo.

    Usage is as per the paradigm outlined for PredictiveInfoCalculator, with:

    • The constructor step being a simple call to PredictiveInfoCalculatorKernel();
    • Additional initialisation options initialise(int, double) and initialise(int, int, double); and
    • PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo.setProperty(String, String) allowing properties for MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKernel.setProperty(String, String) (except MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariate.PROP_TIME_DIFF as outlined in PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo.setProperty(String, String))

    References:

    • Bialek, W., Nemenman, I., and Tishby, N., "Complexity through nonextensivity", Physica A, 302, 89-99. (2001).
    • J. P. Crutchfield, D. P. Feldman, "Regularities Unseen, Randomness Observed: Levels of Entropy Convergence", Chaos, Vol. 13, No. 1. (2003), pp. 25-54.
    Author:
    Joseph Lizier (email, www)
    See Also:
    PredictiveInfoCalculator, PredictiveInfoCalculatorViaMutualInfo, MutualInfoCalculatorMultiVariateKernel
